&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Director of Infrastructure &amp;amp; SRE owns the function end-to-end: reliability, security, scalability, and operational governance of TailorCare’s infrastructure, plus the team that delivers it. You will be a peer to the Director of Software Engineering, Director of Data Engineering, and Director of Data Science, own the Infrastructure &amp;amp; SRE scorecard in front of the executive team, and lead vendor escalations with Salesforce, AWS, and Cresta, among others, at the Director level.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a player-coach role. In year one you will spend roughly 60% of your time hands-on (writing Terraform, leading incidents, doing architecture work) and 40% building the team and the practice. As the team scales, that ratio shifts toward leadership, but you will never stop being technical.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is not a slideware role. We are not hiring a manager who reviews architecture diagrams from a distance. We are hiring an operator who codes, runs incidents, owns the platform, and ships&lt;/p&gt;
